content.solution_latex:
We can divide the polygon into 25 squares.

[asy]
unitsize(0.5 cm);

draw((3,0)--(4,0));
draw((2,1)--(5,1));
draw((1,2)--(6,2));
draw((0,3)--(7,3));
draw((0,4)--(7,4));
draw((1,5)--(6,5));
draw((2,6)--(5,6));
draw((3,7)--(4,7));
draw((0,3)--(0,4));
draw((1,2)--(1,5));
draw((2,1)--(2,6));
draw((3,0)--(3,7));
draw((4,0)--(4,7));
draw((5,1)--(5,6));
draw((6,2)--(6,5));
draw((7,3)--(7,4));
[/asy]

Let the side length of each square be $s$.  Then the perimeter of the polygon is $28s = 56$, so $s = 2$.  Hence, the area of the polygon is $25s^2 = \boxed{100}$.

